 the bloomberg terminal risk and compliance operations can expect data consistency trading and monitoring trading and monitoring global regulations put in place over the last decade emphasize the need for trade compliance throughout the trade lifecycle regulators are asking firms to perform pretrade analysis execute trades in a transparent manner and perform posttrade checks basel iii  collateral tagging solution basel iii mandated global standards on the levels and types of collateral banks are required to hold as well as segregation arrangements designed to ensure timely and accurate separation of collateral for noncentrally cleared otc derivatives bloomberg’s collateral tagging solution provides customers with an efficient mechanism to determine classify and comply with the collateral eligibility requirements of the noncentrally cleared otc derivatives margin rule across various global regimes the solution is based on extrapolating the regulatory requirements regulatory expertise and industry feedback thus providing a standardized accurate and consistent classification and haircut for eligible collateral across the industry eliminating the guesswork for the firms’ capital and collateral managers doddfrankvolcker rule  covered funds solution the volcker rule requires all us banks and foreign banking organizations fbos to divest ownership interest in “covered funds” these funds may include hedge funds private equity funds collateralized loan obligations clos and other securitizations bloomberg’s covered funds solution helps institutions identify covered funds affected by the volcker rule quickly and efficiently with minimal manual effort built in conjunction with industry stakeholders our identification solution uses nearly  data fields to automatically extract pertinent details from securitization clo and cdo deal documents and classify securities against the requirements of the volcker rule covered funds regulations mifid ii  mifid ii transparency solution mifid ii aims to increase transparency in the fixed income and otc markets as well as improve business and investor protection practices bloomberg’s mifid ii transparency solution provides an automated data feed with  fields covering approximately seven million instruments across numerous asset classes helping support firms’ mifid ii obligations for both pre and posttrade transparency talk to a specialist contact us capital and liquidity in an effort to ensure that firms reduce systemic risk regulators have imposed stricter risk management and capital adequacy measures firms are now required to calculate and manage capital ratios perform risk calculation and reporting carry out stress tests based on the scenarios prescribed by sec e ccar finra and ecbeba guidelines classify eligible liquid assets and quantify liquidity risk to support liquidity ratio calculations eg lcr and nsfr sec e  liquidity assessment solution bloomberg liquidity assessment lqa is an awardwinning solution that enables you to quantitatively evaluate market liquidity across multiple asset classes including government and agency debt corporate bonds municipal bonds global equities and etfs bloomberg lqa meets the regulatory requirements of sec e and adds value to risk management and investment processes using a datadriven approach so you can evaluate liquidity across your enterprise covering  million global securities lqa provides the fund industry with a bestpractice approach to assess market liquidity and to consistently evaluate manage and report liquidity risk across multiassetclass portfolios basel iii  highquality liquid assets solution one of the key reforms of basel iii is the liquidity coverage ratio lcr that requires banks to hold an adequate amount of unencumbered highquality liquid assets hqla that can be converted easily and immediately into cash in private markets bloomberg’s hqla solution offers a set of data points to assist clients in complying with basel iii’s lcr requirements and regulatory reporting eg fr a reporting in the us and common reporting corep in the eu this data which firms can also leverage for calculating their standardized credit risk capital requirements is available via bloomberg’s enterprise data feed which supports both batch requests as well as bulk offerings our hqla solution is scalable and can be customized to clients’ specific needs basel iii  central bank eligibility solution among major central banks there are no consistent standards for securities accepted as eligible collateral some central banks provide detailed lists of eligible securities while others offer only basic guidelines central bank eligibility cbe data from bloomberg eliminates the need for this repetitive manual process it provides essential details about all securities accepted as collateral by  major global central banks bloomberg updates the list of eligible assets daily with haircuts and delivers a consolidated enterprise data feed for each asset category the data is also available on a persecurity basis basel iii  ssfa for securitizations all banks with more than  billion in total assets must adopt the ssfa to calculate risk and capital adequacy the new requirements measure a combination of the collateral performance and structural integrity of every securitization including mortgage and assetbacked securities bloomberg’s solution assists banks in calculating riskweights and capital adequacy requirements in accordance with us basel iii simplified supervisory formula approach it provides the final securitization risk weight factor srwf for nonagency mbs cmbs and abs ssfa calculations are extremely dataintensive requiring both structural and collateral database as well as the ability to compute very large amounts of data bloomberg’s ssfa uses the  data fields needed to calculate the securitization risk weight factor for rmbs cmbs and abs according to basel iii bloomberg offers ssfa analytics on more than  structured products across rmbs cmbs and abs this information can be provided in a bulk push delivery for wider coverage and as a persecurity pull on terminal for targeted security populations solvency ii  solvency ii solution solvency ii requires eu insurers to assess different types of balance sheet risks and maintain a minimum solvency level bloomberg’s solution delivers the data fields required for the qrt reporting of the asset exposures the solution combines high quality reference data with proven expertise in solvency ii taxonomy giving insurers a faster and more cost effective way of maintaining pillar iii compliance the solution provides approximately  data fields that are mapped to the european insurance and occupational pensions authority’s eiopa quantitative reporting templates qrt for insurers these fields are also mapped to the tripartite template so that insurers’ asset managers can also provide data for pillar iii reporting the data is delivered on a persecurity basis frtb  frtb solution the fundamental review of the trading book frtb is the biggest global sellside regulatory change in more than two decades completely overhauling the framework for market risk the pressure is on for hundreds of banks to decide on an frtb solution in  in order to gain regulatory approval before the  deadline a comprehensive suite of solutions enables you to meet all aspects of the frtb requirements ranging from calculation engines to “real price” data repositories whether you require frtbready data a reliable risk analytics engine or a full endtoend workflow bloomberg can customize a package to meet your needs new capabilities include regulatory capital calculations for both standardized and internal model approaches as well as risk factor mapping and modellable risk factor determination—all powered by bloomberg pricing and market data comprehensive capital analysis and review ccar  cca calculation services solution due to heightened regulatory standards the federal reserve board frb either mandates for complex banks or suggests for noncomplex banks usage of both primarychampion models as well as benchmarkchallenger models in the capital planning process bloomberg supports specific quantitative components of comprehensive capital analysis and review ccar by allowing customers to utilize bloomberg calculation service to input their own custom data for each scenario and leverage bloomberg’s market leading analytics to get back critical modeled data such as projected cash flows that are required for ccar stress testing tax and accounting to maintain transparency in capital markets regulators require firms to provide detailed information on their trading systems trade and valuation reporting capital plan and accounting approaches this is mandated globally from sec and finra in the u s to eba and esma in europe with regulations including emir aifmd form pf eba prudent valuation and more ifrs   sppi and expected credit loss solution in july  the international accounting standards board iasb issued ifrs  financial instruments replacing ias  the standard updates the model for balance sheet classification and measurement of financial instruments impairment of financial securities and hedge accounting ifrs  is effective for annual periods beginning on or after january   with early adoption permitted bloomberg’s ifrs  sppi test solution assists clients in performing the contractual cash flows test required by the updated ifrs  classification and measurement model the solution automates the process of reviewing individual security prospectuses and legal documents by scanning over  unique security attributes for each financial instrument and identifying potentially nonsppi features or cash flows intesa sanpaolo selects bloomberg ifrs  sppi data to streamline adoption of new accounting standard view the press announcement our expected credit loss ecl accounting solution saves you significant time money and manpower not as a oneoff but continuously as credit risk models need to be validated and enhanced annually with bloomberg you no longer need to hire large numbers of credit risk personnel build credit risk models or bolster the accounting department’s resources to interpret and implement ifrs  components bloomberg’s ecl solution is an implementationready product that provides the necessary transparency to management ias  gaap  fair value hierarchy leveling tool solution effective  any reporting entity that is subject to ias international accounting standards or us gaap generally accepted accounting principles has to disclose assets in the fair value hierarchy bloomberg’s fair value hierarchy leveling tool fvhl tool enables clients to customize and store their own rules to determine fair value leveling results either   or  at a certain point in time while aligning with the high quality independent evaluated price provided by bloomberg valuation service bval the market data used to drive the fvhl tool is the identical underlying data used by bval to price each fixed income security the fvhl tool helps clients respond to the accounting requirements set forth by asc  and ifrs  as they extend beyond the original fair value reporting standards fas  and ias  asc   ifrs  pricing transparency solution the accounting standards asc  fair value measurement in the us and ifrs  fair value measurement internationally require increased disclosures around the sources inputs and methodology used to calculate the fair value of financial instruments presented in the financial statements a key component of both of these standards is the requirement for companies to include a “leveling” table in the notes to the financial statements which classifies all investments presented at fair value as level   or  based on the significance of unobservable inputs bloomberg’s pricing transparency  leveling tools provide an objective consistent and defensible solution for many of the regulatory and accounting issues facing our clients today by exposing the underlying market data used in the bval pricing models irs section m solution the us internal revenue service irs regulation under section m requires withholding on certain notional principal contracts derivatives and other equitylinked instruments with payments that reference dividends on us equity securities and indices withholding is required when those amounts are paid to a nonus person contracts linked to equity indexes are deemed to be in scope based on whether the index is categorized as “qualified” or “nonqualified” in addition the delta of a contract at issuance the ratio comparing the change in price of an underlying asset to the change in price of a derivative must be  or higher discover how m will impact your daytoday operations bloomberg’s data solution for m facilitates identification of inscope instruments providing high quality delta calculations and test indices for qualification stamp act solution handling taxes imposed by global authorities can be a serious challenge for financial firms many international broker dealers and wealth managers for example deal with taxeligible securities on behalf of clients but remain responsible for remitting payments to relevant authorities to streamline this process firms first need an efficient and dependable way to identify tax and levyeligible instruments and map them to security databases this requires both a comprehensive security master database and the ability to monitor daily fluctuations in eligibility as new listings and delistings take place bloomberg’s stamp tax solution helps financial firms identify eligible instruments quickly accurately and dynamically drawing on bloomberg’s vast data resources this solution provides updated eligibility data at the security level it offers complete mapping between the relevant tax datasets and our comprehensive reference database which helps ensure extensive coverage of eligible securities with this daily file firms gain access to the data required to calculate payments properly comply with tax requirements and avoid unexpected liability fatca solution the foreign account tax compliance act fatca requires foreign financial institutions ffis to register and report information about us taxpayers to the irs in addition ffis must either withhold tax on transactions that involve specific eligible instruments or pay an equivalent penalty the bloomberg fatca withholding solution offers a more streamlined approach for ffis drawing on our unparalleled data resources—including industrystandard terms and conditions corporate actions and entity data—the solution provides fatcaspecific securitylevel details for instruments across fixed income equity muni and mortgage asset classes consolidating this data in one solution helps firms identify affected instruments quickly and accurately what we offer bloomberg terminal bloomberg tradebook execution and order management data and content financial data management integration and distribution on this page regulationready data trading and monitoring capital and liquidity tax and accounting insights sending colony capital iii lp  santa monica ca search colony capital iii lp  santa monica ca searching access information of millions of companies using our advanced search technology that provides accurate and segmented results companies all across america search by industry city state sic or naics code to obtain a customized list of business that fits exactly what you are looking for search everything find up to date contact information including address phone and fax number email and company website our business entity directory consists of more than  million companies registered in the united states find companies by industry sector or address whether you are looking for specific information about a company or researching industries leads or new potential customers and clients findusabusinesscom is the right place for you to help you refine your results we offer several search selections including city state zip code sic o